Package: sampEstimator
Title: Estimate sample sizes for reliable detection with an imperfect test
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Robert",
           family = "Link",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "ard"),
           email = "rliz@virginia.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7071-248X"))
Description: 
    Estimate the sample size required to reliably detect the spread of a disease
    (for suitable definition of "reliable").  The calculation is performed taking
    into account finite population size and type I and type II errors in the test.
